  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6594.66 sitting directly between max negative gamma at 6590 (-26.6B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+24.7B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any rally toward 6605. The massive negative GEX clustering around current levels (6580-6590) creates amplifying conditions where dealer hedging will accelerate moves in either direction, while the strong positive gamma wall at 6605 acts as magnetic resistance. The recent GEX surge event combined with -22.8% 1-minute change suggests dealers are actively hedging short gamma positions, creating whipsaw conditions in this tight 15-point range.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent ping-pong action between 6590 support and 6605 resistance until one side breaks decisively.",
